        <h2>Definitions</h2>
        <p><b>Non-Fungible Token:</b> A unique, blockchain-based digital asset that represents ownership of specific items or content, such as art, collectibles, or virtual property.</p>
        <p><b>Plot, Digital Asset, Crypto Asset:</b> A non-fungible token that represents a discrete unit of digital land within a virtual world. Users can upload and manage a "build" (a user generated voxel structure) associated with the Plot as well as other properties (such as a name, description, and link).</p>
        <p><b>Subplot:</b> A Plot that exists as a subordinate or nested unit within another Plot. Its designation as a Subplot is defined by its relationship to the overarching Plot in which it resides, and not by intrinsic properties that would differentiate it from any other plot at any other depth.</p>
        <p><b>Parent Plot:</b> A Plot that acts as a container for one or more Subplots. A Parent Plot is defined by its relationship to its Subplots, serving as their immediate superior within the nesting structure.</p>
        <p><b>Depth:</b> The hierarchical level of a Plot or Subplot within the virtual world. Depth is determined by the number of nesting levels above a given Plot. For example, a top-level Plot resides at Depth 0, its immediate Subplots are at Depth 1, and further nested Subplots are at increasing Depths. The current maximum depth is Depth 2 and is subject to change.</p>
        <p><b>Mint Price:</b> the price in ethereum to introduce a new token into the total supply. This value is set by us for Depth 0 Plots and parent plot owners for all other plots.</p>
        <p><b>Crypto Wallet, Wallet:</b> A digital tool for storing, managing, and transacting cryptocurrency and blockchain-based assets, including tokens and NFTs. It also enables access to decentralized applications.</p>
        <p><b>Smart Contract:</b> A self-executing program on the Ethereum blockchain that automatically enforces agreements and transactions based on predefined conditions.</p>
        <p><b>Marketplace:</b> A platform for buying, selling, or trading digital assets, such as NFTs or crypto assets, often using blockchain technology.</p>
        <p><b>User, You:</b> Any individual accessing the website whether that individual has connected a wallet or not and whether that individual engages any of the services or not.</p>
